Friday Olokor, Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday congratulated Ethiopian Prime Minister, Abiy Ahmed, who was declared winner of 2019 Nobel Peace Prize in Oslo, Norway. The President said such a feat was a reflection of a good sign for the peace processes within countries, and across borders on African continent. Buhari’s felicitation was contained in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina. He said, “President Buhari felicitates with the Prime Minister, his cabinet and all Ethiopians on the remarkable global recognition of winning the 100th peace prize, which was attributed to a decision to end 20-year conflict between two African countries, Ethiopia and Eritrea.” Copyright PUNCH.
